53 season Ranger.

..and thats an "E" at the end, not a "D".........</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#7c96b9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub88.ezboard.com/uelomar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elomar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/18/01 1:06:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Off hand</span><hr size=1> Right the off hand does have its own delay and wont go off till time is up. Lets say in some magical land the wurmslayer went into your off hand (cause I cant think of a high delay offhander right now) and you had a lammy in your primary.<br>
you attack..you swing the lammy and make the duel save so you swing the wurm too. Delay goes by for the lammy so you swing it again and again make the duel save for the secondary but because the 40 delay on the wurm isnt up yet it doesnt swing. You have to wait till the next primary swing and a successful duel wield. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#1478A2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub88.ezboard.com/bepicheroes73161.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=amanar>Amanar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/18/01 2:03:56 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Off hand</span><hr size=1> Yesh i was in the group, and like stupie, i asked wut he was smokin, cuz damn i need sum of that. Offhand is COMPLETELY independent. He was refering to my wurmy and lammy. I am POSITIVE my lammy hits more often than my wurmy, unless my wurmy is super fast!  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#7c96b9><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub88.ezboard.com/uriphen.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Riphen</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/19/01 10:27:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub88.ezboard.com/fepicheroes73161frm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=24.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Off hand</span><hr size=1> From what I've read in multiple threads on monkly business, the dly of primary and off hand are completely independent. Off hand dly set at 40 all the time is disproved by swinging two of the same weapon. All 4 hits, assuming dw and da go off, will be in seqence. If you use two different weapons, your primary does not have to swing for a check on dw. If it did, when ever your secondary swings, the hits would come at the same time as the primary. The skill check on dw simply occurs when the dly for your off hand weapon has recycled. If you want to test this, put the faster weapon in your off hand and it should hit multiple times independent of the slower primary weapon.<br>
<br>
Riphen<br>
